# Create a comprehensive .gitignore for Python/ML projects
cat > .gitignore << EOF
# Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# Virtual environments
venv/
env/
.venv/

# Poetry
poetry.lock
# Don't ignore pyproject.toml - we need this!

# Jupyter Notebook
.ipynb_checkpoints

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Large datasets (don't push data to GitHub)
datasets/*.csv
datasets/*.json
!datasets/README.md

# Models
*.pkl
*.model
*.h5
EOF

# Update your README.md
cat > README.md << EOF
# Machine Learning Zoomcamp

My journey through the [Machine Learning Zoomcamp](https://github.com/DataTalksClub/machine-learning-zoomcamp) by Alexey Grigorev.

## Project Structure

- `01-intro/` - Introduction to Machine Learning
- `02-regression/` - Machine Learning for Regression
- `03-classification/` - Machine Learning for Classification
- `04-evaluation/` - Evaluation Metrics for Classification
- `05-deployment/` - Deploying Machine Learning Models
- `06-ensemble/` - Decision Trees and Ensemble Learning
- `07-nn/` - Neural Networks and Deep Learning
- `08-serverless/` - Serverless Deep Learning
- `09-k8s/` - Kubernetes and TensorFlow Serving
- `10-kubeflow/` - Kubernetes and Kubeflow
- `projects/` - Capstone and other projects
- `datasets/` - Data files (gitignored)
- `notes/` - Study notes and documentation
- `scripts/` - Utility scripts

## Setup

\`\`\`bash
# Using Poetry for dependency management
poetry install
poetry shell
\`\`\`
EOF
